Like free beauty products? Yeah, us too. We’ve got good news for you – high-end department store Liberty is looking to hire a beauty tester. The successful applicant will receive a 12-month subscription to Liberty’s Beauty Drop service. This includes four boxes of products per year, with a total value of £300. On top of that, the subscription will also include £240 worth of credit to spend on even more self-care treats. The individual will also have the option to review products, and send the Liberty team their thoughts. The types of brands the selected person will get to try span the skincare, makeup and haircare fields. According to the job ad, these include the likes of Kiehl’s, Augustinus Bader, Sunday Riley, Bobbi Brown, BYREDO. Interested in this exciting opportunity? To apply, you’ve got to be 18 or older and a resident of the UK. If you’ve got those boxes ticked, you can put your name forward in three steps: The retailer will close the entry window at 23.59 on August 15 2022. More information on the role can be found here. Do you have a story to share? Get in touch by emailing MetroLifestyleTeam@Metro.co.uk MORE : The Hot List: Beauty buys from Harry Styles’ nail polish to vegan skincare MORE : Our sweat-proof makeup edit – perfect for a heatwave MORE : Influencer shares six makeup products that are so good they ‘don’t make sense’